=ErcNicks= 

erc-nicks.el is a module that automatically colorizes nicknames.

It can be enabled by adding 'nicks' to erc-modules.

==Customization==

Use 'customize-group erc-nicks' to see configuration options.

You can use 'erc-nicks-refresh' to view your changes.

==User defined nick colors==

If you are going to make 'erc-nicks-colors' a custom list of colors, then you most likely want to 
override 'erc-nicks--create-pool-function' and set it to 'erc-nicks--create-culled-pool', otherwise
the colors will coerce ('erc-nicks--create-coerced-pool') to the nearest terminal color.
<pre>
(setq erc-nicks--create-pool-function 'erc-nicks--create-culled-pool)
</pre>
